image.altText: A before and after shot showing a close-up of Jayden Vilardi before and after he had eight veneers fitted to his top teeth.

props.synopsis: Jayden Vilardi recently spent $21,000 on dental veneers to fix his smile and confidence. He says he did not rush into it and was told of the risks — but there are concerns many others are being enticed by persuasive advertising.

title.children: Dental veneers usually last 10 to 15 years. But patients are not all being told the true cost of the perfect smile

image.altText: People in the water and on the sand at a crowded beach during sunset.

props.synopsis: Western Australia just sweltered through its hottest summer on record, and there are concerns autumn will see some records fall as well.

title.children: After WA's hottest ever summer, forecasters warn it could be 'scary' vision of the future

image.altText: A teenage boy with long brown hair, a black shirt and brown cap and glasses sitting at a desk drawing a picture.

props.synopsis: Macklyn Woollard is one of more than 200,000 people living with autism in Australia. Despite the size of the neurodiverse community, the WA teenager says he struggles to find like-minded people being celebrated in the media.

image.altText: A man stands on a wharf with his crossed arms.

image.altText: A close up of Kate Middleton smiling while wearing dangly earings.

title.children: The House of Windsor has long contended with wild conspiracy theories, but the frenzy around Kate's health is beyond public interest
